  Pots (pots.kicad_sch)

  7× identical subcircuits — one per parameter (Time, Repeats, Mix, Filter, Grit, ModSpd, ModDep):
  3V3 ──┬── POT wiper ── ADCn
        └── 100nF to GND  (anti-aliasing / debounce)
  GND ──┘
  - Part: Alpha 9mm vertical, 10kΩ linear (RV09 series)
  - Wiper connected to ADC pin through 1kΩ series resistor (protect ADC from shorts)

  Controls (controls.kicad_sch)

  - Encoder (EC11 compatible): A→D0, B→D1, SW→D2, with 10kΩ pull-ups to 3V3 and 100nF to GND on each line
  - Bypass footswitch (SPST momentary, 3PDT or SPST since relay handles audio): → D3, 10kΩ pull-up + 100nF
  - Tap footswitch (SPST momentary): → D4, 10kΩ pull-up + 100nF

  Audio I/O (io.kicad_sch)

  - Input jack (Neutrik NMJ6HCD2 or Switchcraft 12B): tip → Daisy IN_L, sleeve → GND
  - Output jack: Daisy OUT_L → tip
  - Relay bypass (G5V-1 5V SPDT): controlled by D5 via NPN transistor (2N3904 + 1kΩ base resistor + flyback diode). Relay routes input directly to output when bypassed.
  - Bypass LED: D6 → 470Ω resistor → LED anode → GND

  MIDI (midi.kicad_sch)

  Standard DIN-5 / TRS Type-A passive input circuit:
  TRS tip  → 220Ω → pin 5 of 6N138
  TRS ring → 220Ω → pin 4 of 6N138 (with 1N4148 protection diode)
  6N138 pin 6 (output) → 3V3 pull-up (4.7kΩ) → D14 (UART1 RX)

  ---
  Grounding Strategy

  - Single ground plane; audio ground and digital ground meet at one star point near the Daisy AGND pin
  - Input jack sleeve is the audio ground reference; digital ground tied at the power connector

  Suggested PCB Form Factor

  - ~100 × 50 mm — fits a 1590BB enclosure
  - Daisy Seed on daughter headers (2× 20-pin), pots/jacks on panel edge
